Now I see the issue clearly. The `handle_fixture_score` function at line 439 gets `sample` as `Option<usize>` from `--sample` flag. If no `--sample` flag is provided, `sample` is `None`, and `score_fixture_suite` scores ALL tasks (line 429-430: `suite.tasks.iter().collect()`). Each task runs bash commands, so 30 tasks × average runtime = timeout.

The fix from issue #49: when the user doesn't provide `--sample N`, default to `Some(5)` (score at most 5 random fixtures).

